Dont know where to start. So first of all the service was really bad they had us come up to the bar to order food and get drinks. Which I found weird but I did it  and order a few shots, a couple beers and an order of mini empanadas. The drinks were way over priced and so was the food. The bartenders and server were of no help and honestly I feel like they didn’t know what they were doing, felt like they were amateur. The food came over an hour later and instead of mini chicken empanadas  they gave me one empanada shaped as a hotdog that was filled with everything expect chicken. I honestly hope we didn’t get food poisoning. Also we saw rats while waiting for the food.  Overall the place looked like it was going to be a secret gem, but it turned out to be one of the worst place we have ever been to.

Super cute spot and great for the outdoor space to just sit and have a drink. Its a cool date spot as well and really chill. It took us a long time to get served, they do have a waitstaff but we finally went inside to order our drinks after about half an hour.  The patio is pretty large with about 7-8 tables and they have a large table in the back for bigger groups. It's not loud (don't think popping music) but like a relaxed patio experience. I tried the Ginger lemon basil drink which was perfect for the day and my friend got the watermelon drink which was a little over-lemoned for my taste, but he liked it.

If 0 stars was available, this place of business would get it.  Can't believe how rude this gentleman is.  I walked in and asked how much a bottle of seltzer was.  He said it was $3 dollars.  I just asked for some ice water and somebody else gave a small cup with barely any ice.  I walked outside and my phone rang.  I stopped for a moment to take the call and this man came outside to yell at me.  There is an obvious place to sit where I momentarily stopped to take this call from my health care provider and this man yelled, "GET OUT OF HERE - THIS IS A PLACE OF BUSINESS".  How can this heartless man yell at me to get out when I am here with two young children.  DISGUSTING 0 STARS!

The owner is hostile - BEWARE. A few days ago, I had a horrifying experience with the owner Jimi and because of that I will NEVER go back. I arrived ready to drop off a deposit for a community event we’d been planning for many weeks. I still had some final questions about the sound capabilities that I had been told to direct to him. I was surprised when Jimi was unwilling to answer my questions despite the fact that the bar was open and completely empty except for me. When I raised this point, he quickly escalated the situation by interrupting me and responding with real rage: “YOUR PARTY IS CANCELLED! YOUR BUSINESS IS NO LONGER WELCOME HERE - GET OUT!” As you can imagine I was shocked and shaken. Given the inoffensive nature of my question, I can only assume some prejudice to my age, gender or race was behind his actions (or some sort of emotional volatility). I would caution all to be wary of this spot and the people who run it.
